definition.value: A 2-hydroxy carboxylic acid that is lactic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by a 4-hydroxyphenyl group.
Any carboxylic ester obtained by the O-acylation of carnitine.
A 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxy group of (S)-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylic acid.
A monoglyceride in which the acyl substituent is located at position 2.
